full_description:

Speaker: Daniel Rios

Track:PyConDE
Keyboards, the main way we interact with computers, have remained unchanged for a century, despite being free from mechanical necessity. Alternatives made possible by recent technology can optimize the way we input text and interact with our devices.

Recorded at the PyConDE & PyData Berlin 2019 conference.
https://pycon.de

More details at the conference page: https://de.pycon.org/program/WJGCNV
Twitter:  https://twitter.com/pydataberlin
Twitter:  https://twitter.com/pyconde
